summary:
Capital Raising Announcement Summary:

  • Structure: Renounceable rights issue ($9m) + Placement to cornerstone investor Amari Metals ($6m minimum, up to $15m total). Oversubscription facility possible (max $24m raised).
  • Pricing: $0.03 per share.
  • Outcome: Amari to own 51% post-capital raise.
  • Key Dates: Shareholder meeting expected late August 2025; offer documentation sent early August 2025.
  • New Debt Facility: 3-year loan agreed with existing syndicate member (same pricing as current facility).
  • Conditions: Shareholder approval, final banking docs, and cross-completion required.

AFT Pharmaceuticals – June Quarter FY26 Investor Update Summary

  • Combogesic IV (Maxigesic IV) launched in Canada – Sales commence as part of North American expansion strategy.
  • Extended US licensing agreement with Hikma Pharmaceuticals – Covers both Combogesic IV and Rapid tablet, restructuring profit-sharing to direct quarterly payments.
  • R&D pipeline progress:
  • Antibiotic eyedrop: Pre-IND filed with FDA, IND targeted by year-end.
  • Strawberry Birthmarks topical: Pre-IND filing planned this year.
  • Novel iron injection: IND filing expected by year-end.
  • Paediatric Maxigesic IV study in preparation – Aims to expand approved patient population.
  • Five out-licensing deals completed – Additional agreements under negotiation.

No capital raising, financial figures, or material trading-sensitive dates identified.

• Capital Structure Change:
  • CIP1 Equity Securities: 85,341,018 unquoted securities redeemed at NZ$1.00 each (total NZ$85.3M).
  • CIP1 Warrants: 7,561,881 unquoted warrants cancelled (nil consideration).

  • Debt Securities: NZ$85.3M repaid.

  • Impact:

  • Reduces outstanding CIP1 Equity Securities by 18.5% (remaining: 376.7M).
  • Reduces outstanding CIP1 Warrants by 43.3% (remaining: 9.9M).

  • No treasury stock held post-transaction.

  • Reason: Mandatory redemption triggered by dividend eligibility (effective 30 June 2025).

Note: Transaction involves unquoted securities; no direct market liquidity impact.

- Final dividend amount (NZD): NZD 0.1325 per share (AUD 0.1229 equivalent).
- Record date: 12/6/2025 | Ex-date: 11/6/2025 | Payment date: 2/7/2025.
- DRP strike price: NZD 10.42983548 per share (2% discount applied).
- DRP election deadline: 13/6/2025 15:00 NZ time.
- Unfranked dividend (100%), withholding tax rate: 15%.
